WEBVTT

00:00.860 --> 00:02.304
- MY WATER JUST BROKE.

00:02.340 --> 00:04.331
[moans]
- IS SHE CLOSE?

00:04.380 --> 00:05.472
- [screams]
- BEAUTIFUL BABY GIRL.

00:05.520 --> 00:08.341
- THIS IS NORA.

00:08.380 --> 00:11.417
- WELL, I HARDLY KNOW HER,
AND I ASKED HER FOR HER BABY.

00:11.450 --> 00:13.486
- OKAY, WHAT'S GOING ON?
- WE'RE GOING TO THE HOSPITAL.

00:13.530 --> 00:15.521
- YOU'RE REALLY NICE.

00:15.560 --> 00:17.141
IF YOU STILL--IF YOU STILL WANT
TO HAVE MY BABY,

00:17.180 --> 00:19.148
YOU CAN HAVE IT.

00:19.190 --> 00:20.452
- BACK IN TOWN, HUH?
YOU'RE DRUNK.

00:20.500 --> 00:22.468
WHAT HAPPENED?
- I QUIT THE BAND.

00:22.500 --> 00:24.081
- GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE!
- DAD, NO!

00:24.120 --> 00:25.428
SETH.

00:25.470 --> 00:26.676
OH, NO.

00:26.710 --> 00:29.429
- YOU CAME.

00:30.440 --> 00:34.308
- WHAT HAPPENED?

00:34.340 --> 00:36.786
- JUST...

00:36.820 --> 00:38.754
DUMB BAR FIGHT.

00:38.790 --> 00:41.827
- WHO GETS
IN A DUMB BAR FIGHT ANYMORE?

00:41.860 --> 00:45.170
YOU'RE NOT 18.
- I KNOW.

00:45.210 --> 00:48.213
OH, THANK YOU
FOR TAKING CARE OF ME.

00:49.840 --> 00:52.354
YOU'RE ALWAYS LOOKING OUT
FOR ME, HUH?

00:59.570 --> 01:01.879
I APPRECIATE IT.

01:01.920 --> 01:03.672
- WHEN IS THIS GONNA STOP?

01:03.710 --> 01:06.645
- IT'S JUST A STUPID BAR FIGHT.

01:06.680 --> 01:07.817
- NO, NO, NO.

01:07.860 --> 01:09.816
THIS...

01:09.860 --> 01:14.581
THIS WHOLE THING'S
GOT TO STOP.

01:14.620 --> 01:17.134
NO, DON'T SMOKE.
DON'T SMOKE IN THE HOUSE.

01:22.150 --> 01:25.790
[melancholy music]

01:25.840 --> 01:26.864
- HEY, ARE THE KIDS HERE?

01:26.910 --> 01:30.141
I'D LIKE TO TAKE 'EM
TO BREAKFAST OR SOMETHING.

01:33.190 --> 01:35.875
- ARE YOU CRAZY?

01:35.920 --> 01:37.296
- I MEAN,
ARE THEY HERE,

01:37.330 --> 01:39.127
OR DID THEY EAT ALREADY?

01:39.160 --> 01:42.470
- DO YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU LOOK LIKE?

01:44.720 --> 01:47.894
SETH, YOU NEED HELP.

01:47.930 --> 01:49.818
- [sighs]
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

01:49.860 --> 01:52.420
I GO'I'I'A GO.

01:52.450 --> 01:54.862
- WAIT, DO YOU KNOW THAT?

01:58.600 --> 02:02.878
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY YEARS
I'VE BEEN CLEANING YOU UP?

02:05.500 --> 02:07.468
IF YOU DON'T GET HELP,

02:07.500 --> 02:11.914
YOU CAN'T SEE
THESE CHILDREN ANYMORE.

02:11.950 --> 02:13.838
IF I HAVE TO GET
A RESTRAINING ORDER,

02:13.890 --> 02:15.812
THAT'S WHAT I WILL DO.
- WILL YOU JUST CALM DOWN?

02:15.850 --> 02:16.748
- NO, I WILL NOT CALM DOWN.
YOUR LIFE IS A MESS.

02:16.790 --> 02:18.849
LOOK AT YOURSELF.
YOUR LIFE IS A MESS,

02:18.890 --> 02:20.403
AND I'M DONE PICKING UP
AFTER YOU.

02:20.450 --> 02:22.918
WHY DON'T YOU SEE
WHAT I SEE?

02:22.970 --> 02:24.346
YOU'RE BLEEDING,
AND YOU WANT

02:24.380 --> 02:25.961
TO TAKE YOUR CHILDREN
TO BREAKFAST?

02:26.000 --> 02:28.275
YOU HAVE TO GO TO REHAB,

02:28.320 --> 02:29.548
OR YOU'RE NOT
SEEING THEM AGAIN.

02:29.590 --> 02:31.933
THAT'S IT.
I'M DONE.

02:51.890 --> 02:54.859
[peaceful music]

03:10.980 --> 03:12.663
- I LOVE THIS BAND.

03:12.700 --> 03:13.769
- YEAH.

03:13.810 --> 03:17.769
YEAH, THEY'RE SORT
OF, LIKE--LIKE THE DECEMBERISTS

03:17.810 --> 03:20.222
MEETS WILD HORSES.

03:20.260 --> 03:22.706
- I CAN SEE THAT.

03:29.070 --> 03:32.756
- HEY, I, UM, I SORT OF RAMMED
MY SHOULDER

03:32.790 --> 03:35.827
THE OTHER DAY.
IT'S REALLY KILLING ME.

03:35.870 --> 03:36.939
WOULD YOU MIND...

03:40.730 --> 03:42.379
RUBBING IT?
- YEAH. YEAH, SURE.

03:42.420 --> 03:44.763
UM, YEAH.

03:44.810 --> 03:46.311
- YEAH, IT'S JUST...

03:46.360 --> 03:47.839
LIKE, RIGHT HERE.

03:47.880 --> 03:49.393
YEAH.

04:05.000 --> 04:06.581
- UM...

04:08.000 --> 04:12.039
YEAH, I SHOULD--
I SHOULD GET YOU

04:12.070 --> 04:14.482
ASPIRIN OR SOMETHING.

04:14.530 --> 04:16.839
I WOULDN'T WANT YOU...

04:20.910 --> 04:23.390
AH...[mutters].

04:23.430 --> 04:25.637
- ALL RIGHT,
THERE THEY ARE!

04:25.670 --> 04:26.910
[laughs]

04:26.950 --> 04:30.954
HEY, WELCOME HOME,
NORA BRAVERMAN.

04:30.990 --> 04:32.332
YOU SWEETH EART.

04:32.370 --> 04:33.712
- HOW WAS IT?
- OH, AND THERE'S MOM.

04:33.750 --> 04:34.717
HEY, MOM.
HOW YOU DOING?

04:34.750 --> 04:36.331
SAY HI.
- NO. NO, ZEEK.

04:36.370 --> 04:38.474
I GOT TO TAKE A SHOWER.
I'M SMELLY.

04:38.510 --> 04:39.898
IT'S OKAY.
- BIG SMILE. THERE'S DAD.

04:39.930 --> 04:40.919
- HEY.
- HERE'S DAD.

04:40.970 --> 04:42.858
[overlapping statements]

04:42.900 --> 04:44.583
- LET MOM GET HER IN.
MAX, MAX.

04:44.620 --> 04:46.724
HEY, MAX, YOU WANT
TO HELP ME, HONEY?

04:46.760 --> 04:47.863
GOOD JOB.

04:47.900 --> 04:48.969
- HI, SWEETH EART.

04:49.010 --> 04:50.932
- JUST GIVE HER ONE SECOND,
SWEETS.

04:50.980 --> 04:52.834
- I WANT TO HOLD HER.
NO, I WANT TO HOLD HER NOW.

04:52.870 --> 04:54.565
- YOU CAN HOLD HER
IN A MOMENT, OKAY?

04:54.600 --> 04:55.976
- YOU GUYS SAID
I COULD HOLD HER.

04:56.010 --> 04:57.398
- HONEY, YOU'RE GONNA HOLD HER
IN A SECOND.

04:57.430 --> 04:59.421
- LET'S GO GET SOMETHING
OUT OF THE CAR.

04:59.470 --> 05:00.949
- CAN YOU GRAB THE BALLOONS
AND MY PURSE?

05:00.990 --> 05:03.322
- OKAY, PURSE, BALLOONS,
PLANTS.

05:03.370 --> 05:04.678
GOT IT.
- WOW, YOU KNOW, ADAM...

05:04.710 --> 05:05.677
- THAT'S OKAY.

05:05.710 --> 05:06.574
- SHE LOOKS JUST LIKE YOU.

05:06.610 --> 05:07.952
- DO YOU THINK?
- GOSH, WHAT A SHAME.

05:07.990 --> 05:09.639
- SHE DOESN'T LOOK
ANYTHING LIKE YOU.

05:09.680 --> 05:11.682
THAT'S FOR SURE.
- JUST JOKING.

05:11.720 --> 05:12.948
- WHERE IS SHE?

05:13.000 --> 05:15.651
OH, THERE SHE IS.
- HERE'S THE LITTLE GIRL.

05:15.690 --> 05:18.921
- I'VE KNOWN YOU LONGER
THAN YOUR DAD HAS.

05:18.970 --> 05:20.619
- ALL RIGHT, KNOCK IT OFF.

05:20.660 --> 05:22.457
GIVE IT A REST.

05:22.490 --> 05:23.934
- HEY, ADAM.
- WHAT?

05:23.970 --> 05:25.073
- CAN I TALK TO YOU
ABOUT SOMETHING REAL QUICK?

05:25.110 --> 05:28.876
- OKAY.

05:28.910 --> 05:31.014
- SHE'S SMILING AT ME.

05:31.050 --> 05:32.460
- WHAT, IS SOMETHING WRONG?

05:32.500 --> 05:34.843
- JERRY RAGAVOY IS DEAD.

05:34.880 --> 05:36.529
- OH, MY GOD,
I'M SORRY.

05:36.570 --> 05:37.912
- WELL, YOU DON'T NEED
TO BE SORRY.

05:37.950 --> 05:39.019
I DON'T KNOW HIM.
- WHO IS HE?

05:39.060 --> 05:40.880
- YOU DON'T KNOW WHO JERRY--

05:40.920 --> 05:42.649
HE'S A HUGE SONGWRITER.

05:42.680 --> 05:43.886
REALLY, REALLY EPIC.
- OKAY.

05:43.920 --> 05:45.785
- YOU KNOW, YOU'RE
IN THE MUSIC INDUSTRY NOW,

05:45.820 --> 05:47.378
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO LEARN THIS STUFF EVENTUALLY.

05:47.410 --> 05:48.820
- ALL RIGHT.
- SO A BUNCH OF ARTISTS

05:48.860 --> 05:50.088
ARE GONNA DO A TRIBUTE ALBUM,
AND ONE OF THEM

05:50.140 --> 05:51.653
WANTS TO RECORD
AT OUR STUDIO.

05:51.690 --> 05:52.850
- REALLY? THAT'S GREAT.
WELL, WHO?

05:52.900 --> 05:54.754
- GOD, I HOPE
YOU KNOW THIS NAME.

05:54.800 --> 05:55.755
CEE LO GREEN.

05:55.800 --> 05:57.768
- CEE LO--
YEAH.

05:57.800 --> 05:58.835
CEE LO GREEN.
- OH, GOOD, GOOD, GOOD.

05:58.870 --> 06:00.098
- FORGET YOU.
- YEAH, FORGET YOU.

06:00.150 --> 06:01.424
YOU GOT IT.
- DUDE.

06:01.460 --> 06:03.007
- YEAH, DUDE.
- THIS IS AWESOME.

06:03.050 --> 06:04.938
- I KNOW.
BUT...

06:04.980 --> 06:06.459
- WE'RE NOT READY.
- NO.

06:06.500 --> 06:07.706
NOWHERE CLOSE TO READY.

06:07.740 --> 06:08.911
THAT'S WHAT I TOLD THE GUY,

06:08.950 --> 06:09.735
BUT I WANTED TO COME HERE
AND CLEAR IT

06:09.780 --> 06:11.805
WITH YOU
BEFORE I TOLD THE GUY NO.

06:11.850 --> 06:13.670
- NO, NO, NO, NO,
YOU CAN'T SAY NO.

06:13.710 --> 06:14.847
- BUT WE'RE NOT READY.
YOU JUST SAID IT.

06:14.890 --> 06:16.084
- NO, NO, WE'RE NOT READY,
BUT WE'RE GONNA BE READY.

06:16.130 --> 06:17.119
WE HAVE TO SEIZE THE DAY.

06:17.160 --> 06:18.889
THIS IS SOMETHING THAT
COULD PUT US ON THE MAP.

06:18.930 --> 06:20.784
OKAY, CROSBY, WE CAN DO THIS.

06:20.820 --> 06:22.026
OKAY?
YOU REMEMBER THE LEMONADE STAND?

06:22.070 --> 06:23.958
REMEMBER THAT?
WE KICKED BU'I'I'.

06:24.000 --> 06:25.137
IT WAS WINTER.
WE HAVE TO GET HIM

06:25.170 --> 06:26.967
IN THE RECORDING STUDIO--
- I LOVE YOUR ENTHUSIASM.

06:27.000 --> 06:29.867
WE HAVEN'T DONE ONE THING--
- WE WILL DEVOTE OURSELVES 24/7.

06:29.900 --> 06:31.413
I CAN DO THIS.
YOU JUST TELL ME

06:31.460 --> 06:32.893
WHAT NEEDS TO BE DONE,
I WILL GET IT DONE.

06:32.940 --> 06:33.861
IF THERE'S ONE THING
I KNOW HOW TO DO, IT'S WORK.

06:33.910 --> 06:35.730
- YOU JUST BROUGHT A BABY HOME.
- I KNOW.

06:35.770 --> 06:37.909
OKAY, BUT THIS IS AN OPPORTUNITY
FROM THE GODS.

06:37.940 --> 06:38.941
WE DO THIS FOR THE BABY.

06:38.980 --> 06:41.733
WE'RE DOING IT
FOR THE WHOLE BRAVERMAN FAMILY.

06:41.780 --> 06:43.736
COME ON, MAN.
THIS IS AMAZING.

06:43.780 --> 06:45.042
- OKAY.
- OKAY?

06:45.090 --> 06:46.569
- OKAY.
- IT'S A BIG DEAL.

06:46.610 --> 06:48.953
- I WILL TRY.
- THIS IS AMAZING.

06:48.990 --> 06:50.605
HEY, EVERYBODY--
- NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

06:50.650 --> 06:51.958
THERE'S NO NEED TO TELL THEM.
- RELAX. RELAX.

06:51.990 --> 06:53.924
EVERYBODY, THIS IS AMAZING.
OKAY?

06:53.960 --> 06:57.020
CROSBY HERE HAS ARRANGED

06:57.070 --> 06:58.788
FOR CEE LO GREEN...

06:58.830 --> 07:01.162
- OH, WOW.
- TO RECORD AT OUR STUDIO.

07:01.210 --> 07:03.724
- NO, NO, NO, MAYBE.
- WHO'S CEE LO GREEN?

07:03.760 --> 07:06.001
- THAT'S WONDERFUL
BRAVERMAN NEWS.

07:06.040 --> 07:07.621
- THAT'S REALLY COOL.
- COME ON. LET'S GET A SHOT.

07:07.660 --> 07:08.627
- I'M EXCITED.

07:08.660 --> 07:10.002
I'M SO TIRED.

07:10.050 --> 07:11.972
- MY SONS GOT
THEIR FIRST CLIENT.

07:12.010 --> 07:12.977
NORA BRAVERMAN'S HOME.

07:13.010 --> 07:15.661
EVERYBODY GOT TO SQUEEZE IN
A LITTLE BIT.

07:15.710 --> 07:18.178
TWO, THREE...
- I LOVE IT.

07:18.230 --> 07:21.461
- CEE LO!
all: CEE LO GREEN.

07:21.510 --> 07:24.263
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

07:24.300 --> 07:26.860
MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

07:26.890 --> 07:28.949
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

07:29.000 --> 07:31.548
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

07:31.580 --> 07:33.969
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

07:34.000 --> 07:36.207
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

07:36.240 --> 07:38.686
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:38.730 --> 07:41.005
FOREVER YOUNG

07:41.040 --> 07:43.861
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

07:43.910 --> 07:45.901
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

07:45.940 --> 07:48.636
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

07:48.670 --> 07:50.706
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

07:50.740 --> 07:53.629
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

07:53.680 --> 07:55.819
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

07:55.850 --> 07:57.841
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:57.890 --> 08:00.529
FOREVER YOUNG

08:00.580 --> 08:02.787
MAY YOU STAY

08:02.820 --> 08:05.926
FOREVER YOUNG

08:09.730 --> 08:10.958
- KENNY, KENNY,
LISTEN, I APPRECIATE THAT,

08:11.000 --> 08:12.558
BUT TOMORROW'S STILL
NOT SOON ENOUGH, OKAY?

08:12.590 --> 08:14.319
WE REALLY NEED TO GET
THAT PIANO IN THERE

08:14.350 --> 08:16.727
BY THE END OF TODAY.
ALL RIGHT?

08:16.770 --> 08:18.829
YEAH. NO, I CAN HOLD.

08:18.870 --> 08:19.973
HAPPY TO HOLD.
OKAY.

08:20.010 --> 08:20.931
- HEY, BABE.
- HEY.

08:20.980 --> 08:22.186
- HONEY, I THOUGHT
YOU GUYS HAD A PIANO.

08:22.220 --> 08:24.074
- WE DO.
WE HAVE AN UPRIGHT,

08:24.120 --> 08:25.109
BUT WE NEED A BABY GRAND.
IT'S A TOTALLY DIFFERENT SOUND.

08:25.150 --> 08:27.220
HEY, WHERE IS THAT BOX
OF WELSH SPRING WATER

08:27.260 --> 08:28.602
THAT I GOT?
REMEMBER THOSE?

08:28.640 --> 08:29.800
- IT'S BY THE BACK DOOR.

08:29.850 --> 08:30.919
THAT STUFF IS REALLY EXPENSIVE.

08:30.950 --> 08:31.939
I WAS LOOKING
AT THE PRICE TAG.

08:31.990 --> 08:33.844
- YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW,
HERE'S THE DEAL, HONEY.

08:33.890 --> 08:35.573
YOU KNOW, IT'S JUST, I'M TRYING
TO BE HIP, CUTTING-EDGE.

08:35.610 --> 08:36.747
WE'RE GONNA MAKE
ALL THE MONEY BACK.

08:36.790 --> 08:37.779
IT'S AN INVESTMENT.
- YUP.

08:37.820 --> 08:38.787
- OKAY, HELLO,
GOOD MORNING.

08:38.820 --> 08:40.060
I'M GOING Ill-(I) SCHOOL.

08:40.100 --> 08:41.579
- I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW

08:41.620 --> 08:43.303
I'M GONNA SEND IN
MY COLLEGE ESSAY.

08:43.350 --> 08:45.068
I JUST DON'T WANT YOU
TO FREAK OUT LATER.

08:45.110 --> 08:46.304
- NO, YOU CAN'T DO THAT.
I HAVE TO LOOK AT IT FIRST

08:46.350 --> 08:47.624
BEFORE YOU SEND IT OUT.
- DO YOU HAVE TIME

08:47.660 --> 08:48.888
TO DO THAT?
- OF COURSE I HAVE TIME.

08:48.940 --> 08:50.248
- AH, I GOT TO GET
THOSE SPEAKERS!

08:50.280 --> 08:51.724
THAT'S GREAT, HONEY.
THANK YOU SO MUCH

08:51.770 --> 08:52.976
FOR DOING THAT FOR HER.
- THEN I'LL PRINT IT OUT

08:53.010 --> 08:54.898
FOR YOU, UH, I DON'T KNOW,
WHEN I GET HOME.

08:54.940 --> 08:55.975
- JUST PRINT IT OUT AND LEAVE IT
EITHER ON MY BED

08:56.010 --> 08:57.216
OR DOWN HERE.
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

08:57.260 --> 08:59.012
- BYE.
- DO YOU WANT TO TAKE THIS?

08:59.050 --> 09:00.153
- ALL RIGHT,
WE GOT THE PIANO.

09:00.190 --> 09:02.351
- YAY.
- I AM OFF TO CONQUER WORLDS.

09:02.400 --> 09:03.981
OKAY?
- ALL RIGHT. VERY EXCITING.

09:04.020 --> 09:05.567
- I DON'T KNOW
WHEN I'M GONNA BE BACK.

09:05.610 --> 09:06.918
IT MIGHT BE DAYS.

09:06.960 --> 09:08.291
- OKAY, I'M LEAVING.
GOOD LUCK.

09:08.340 --> 09:09.466
TELL CEE LO WHAT'S UP.
- LOVE YOU.

09:09.510 --> 09:10.954
- THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR DOING
EVERYTHING YOU DO HERE.

09:10.990 --> 09:12.810
- I'M HAPPY TO SEE YOU
LIKE THIS.

09:12.860 --> 09:14.066
- ...LI'|_|'LE ONE.
MWAH.

09:14.100 --> 09:15.852
YOU'RE A SAINT.
- I AM SO HAPPY TO DO IT.

09:15.900 --> 09:16.924
- HEY, HONEY,
I LOVE YA.

09:16.970 --> 09:18.039
- PROUD OF YOU.

09:18.070 --> 09:19.719
- [laughs]

09:19.760 --> 09:22.752
- [Nora fusses]

09:27.700 --> 09:30.009
- JOEL AND I
ARE ADOPTING A BABY.

09:30.050 --> 09:31.278
[cheers]
- TOLD YOU.

09:31.320 --> 09:32.799
[laughter]

09:32.840 --> 09:34.353
- YOU WERE RIGHT ON.

09:34.400 --> 09:36.186
I OWE HER 50 BUCKS.

09:36.230 --> 09:39.017
- YOU KNOW I'M GONNA COLLECT.
THAT IS SO COOL.

09:39.060 --> 09:40.197
- THAT'S BETTER
THAN A PROMOTION.

09:40.230 --> 09:41.959
IS IT BORN YET?

09:41.990 --> 09:43.639
- NO, HE'S...

09:43.680 --> 09:45.022
both: HE?
- IT'S A BOY.

09:45.060 --> 09:46.288
- IT'S A BOY.

09:46.340 --> 09:47.955
- DELIVER IN A FEW MONTHS.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.059
- SO THE AGENCY
FINALLY CAME THROUGH.

09:50.100 --> 09:51.374
- UM, NO.

09:51.410 --> 09:53.992
THE AGENCY WAS NOT QUITE
VERY HELPFUL AT ALL.

09:54.040 --> 09:56.827
- YOU SWITCHED AGENCIES.

09:56.870 --> 09:58.656
- HOW'D YOU GET HOOKED UP
WITH THE BABY THEN?

09:58.700 --> 10:00.793
- UM...

10:00.840 --> 10:03.934
THERE IS A YOUNG WOMAN
WHO WORKS AT MY OFFICE

10:03.980 --> 10:05.311
WHO IS PREGNANT.

10:05.360 --> 10:07.043
SHE ACT UALLY--
SHE WORKS AT THE COFFEE CART.

10:07.080 --> 10:10.390
AND SHE IS NOT KEEPING
THE BABY.

10:10.430 --> 10:12.705
AND WE ARE ADOPTING IT.

10:12.750 --> 10:14.126
- WOW.
- SO IT'S PRETTY AMAZING.

10:14.160 --> 10:15.775
- A COFFEE CART.
- YOU'RE GETTING A BABY

10:15.820 --> 10:17.082
FROM A COFFEE CART.

10:17.130 --> 10:18.097
DO YOU KNOW HER?

10:18.130 --> 10:19.199
- YOU KNOW WHAT, WE--

10:19.230 --> 10:20.299
- YES.

10:20.340 --> 10:21.989
- TYPICALLY
IN SITUATIONS LIKE THIS,

10:22.030 --> 10:24.089
YOU DON'T REALLY KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THE PARENTS AT ALL.

10:24.140 --> 10:26.131
- RIGHT.
- BUT THE AGENCY KNOWS.

10:26.170 --> 10:27.922
USUALLY.
I MEAN, THEY KNOW SOMETHING.

10:27.970 --> 10:30.109
THEY HAVE BACKGROUND.

10:30.140 --> 10:31.869
- RIGHT.
- SEEMS A LITTLE WEIRD,

10:31.900 --> 10:33.242
THOUGH, DOESN'T IT?

10:33.280 --> 10:35.168
- IT'S DIFFERENT.
- IT'S NOT WEIRD.

10:36.460 --> 10:38.837
- NO.
- BUT YOU HAVE AN AGREEMENT.

10:38.870 --> 10:39.973
- YEAH.
- YEAH, YEAH.

10:40.010 --> 10:42.899
SHE'S AGREED TO LET US ADOPT
HER CHILD.

10:42.950 --> 10:45.043
- LOVELY GIRL.
WE'VE HAD HER OVER HERE.

10:45.090 --> 10:46.045
- SHE ASK YOU FOR MONEY?

10:46.090 --> 10:47.773
- NO.
WE...

10:47.810 --> 10:49.983
WE'RE COVERING
HER MEDICAL EXPENSES,

