22:07.150 --> 22:08.833
TO COME HOME
AT ALL TONIGHT OR...?

22:08.870 --> 22:12.078
- UH, NO.
HONEY, IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

22:12.120 --> 22:14.497
WE'RE GONNA BE SE'ITING UP
UNTIL THEY GET HERE.

22:14.540 --> 22:16.770
YOU KNOW,
I GOT A LOT TO DO,

22:16.810 --> 22:18.949
AND I GOT TO BE HERE
FOR CROSBY, SO...

22:18.990 --> 22:20.150
- OKAY.

22:20.200 --> 22:22.054
NO PROBLEM.
I JUST CALLED

22:22.090 --> 22:25.958
TO SAY THAT I LOVE YOU
AND THAT EVERYTHING'S GREAT.

22:25.990 --> 22:28.129
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

22:28.170 --> 22:30.445
HEY, YOU JUST TELL NORA
THAT I'M DOING THIS FOR HER,

22:30.480 --> 22:32.448
OKAY?
SHE'LL UNDERSTAND.

22:32.480 --> 22:33.993
- I WILL.

22:34.040 --> 22:35.758
BYE.

22:35.800 --> 22:38.007
- GOOD NIGHT.

22:38.040 --> 22:40.099
[beep]

22:40.150 --> 22:43.119
- [sighs]

22:49.120 --> 22:50.109
- [sighs]

22:54.820 --> 22:55.957
- HERE WE GO.
HERE WE GO.

22:55.990 --> 22:56.911
ALL RIGHT.

22:56.960 --> 22:58.814
AND WE MARK THAT.

22:58.860 --> 23:00.782
OKAY.
- YOU ALL SET?

23:00.820 --> 23:03.516
- YUP.
RAGAVOY TRIBUTE, TAKE NINE,

23:03.550 --> 23:04.585
CEE LO GREEN.

23:04.620 --> 23:05.848
- ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS THE ONE.

23:05.900 --> 23:07.856
- ONE, TWO, THREE.

23:07.900 --> 23:08.992
AH.

23:09.040 --> 23:12.009
[Janis Joplin's
Piece of My Heart]

23:27.260 --> 23:29.820
COME ON, COME ON

23:29.850 --> 23:31.989
COME ON

23:32.030 --> 23:33.713
[clears throat]

23:33.750 --> 23:34.956
SORRY, MAN.

23:34.990 --> 23:35.809
- THERE A PROBLEM?

23:35.860 --> 23:38.442
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
I WANT TO SWITCH

23:38.480 --> 23:40.892
THIS OLD MICROPHONE OUT.
I DON'T LIKE HOW IT SOUNDS.

23:40.930 --> 23:43.069
- UH, HAPPY TO DO THAT.

23:43.110 --> 23:44.680
IT SOUNDS GREAT
IN HERE, THOUGH.

23:44.730 --> 23:46.448
YEAH, AWESOME.
YOU WERE SHREDDING IT.

23:46.490 --> 23:48.833
IT'S ON FIRE,
BURNING LIKE A TORCH.

23:48.870 --> 23:50.098
- I MEAN, THAT'S COOL,
BUT IT'S GOT

23:50.150 --> 23:52.869
TO SOUND GOOD
TO ME, GUYS.

23:52.910 --> 23:53.934
- I HEAR WHAT YOU'RE SAYING,
CEE LO.

23:53.980 --> 23:54.765
- THANK YOU.
- OKAY.

23:54.810 --> 23:56.493
YOU KNOW, I'LL SWITCH IT
RIGHT NOW.

23:56.530 --> 23:59.658
- YEAH,
IT DEFINITELY SOUNDED THIN.

23:59.710 --> 24:01.701
- OKAY.

24:01.750 --> 24:03.081
- SAID IT SOUNDED KIND OF THIN?

24:03.130 --> 24:05.121
- YEAH.
- IT SOUNDED GOOD, BUT YEAH.

24:06.990 --> 24:09.811
OKAY, I'M GONNA JUST SEE
IF HE NEEDS A HAND HERE.

24:12.650 --> 24:14.857
HEY, THIS IS ALL NORMAL,
RIGHT?

24:14.900 --> 24:15.969
I MEAN, IT'S COOL, RIGHT?

24:16.000 --> 24:16.989
- I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO TELL YOU, OKAY?

24:17.040 --> 24:18.996
MAYBE THIS IS NORMAL FOR HIM.
MAYBE IT'S NOT.

24:19.040 --> 24:20.007
I DON'T KNOW.

24:20.040 --> 24:21.132
- SO THIS IS NOT NORMAL?

24:21.180 --> 24:23.523
- OKAY.

24:23.560 --> 24:25.448
HERE WE GO.

24:29.810 --> 24:32.665
- HEY, HADDIE.
- HI.

24:32.710 --> 24:35.019
- DID YOU TAKE
YOUR COLLEGE ESSAY BACK?

24:35.050 --> 24:36.256
- YEAH, I TOOK IT BACK.

24:36.300 --> 24:37.915
- OH, WELL, I WANTED
TO READ IT.

24:37.950 --> 24:41.056
- I TOOK IT
'CAUSE YOU WERE SLEEPING ON IT.

24:41.100 --> 24:43.614
- OH.

24:43.650 --> 24:45.572
HONEY, I'M SO TIRED.

24:45.620 --> 24:47.952
I'M TELLING YOU,
I'M SLEEP-DEPRIVED.

24:48.000 --> 24:49.683
YOU CANNOT
TAKE THAT PERSONALLY.

24:49.720 --> 24:50.891
- NO.
I'M NOT TAKING IT PERSONALLY.

24:50.930 --> 24:52.238
I KNOW YOU'RE REALLY TIRED.

24:52.280 --> 24:54.999
UH, THAT'S WHY I DIDN'T ASK YOU
TO DO IT.

24:55.040 --> 24:57.907
- I UNDERSTAND, BUT, HADDIE,
I WANT TO READ IT.

24:57.940 --> 24:59.009
YOU KNOW THAT I WANT
TO READ IT, RIGHT?

24:59.040 --> 25:01.668
[Nora crying]

25:01.700 --> 25:04.009
- YEAH, I KNOW--
- IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

25:04.050 --> 25:06.848
- THERE'S A LOT OF STUFF
GOING ON RIGHT NOW,

25:06.880 --> 25:09.565
AND WE DON'T NECESSARILY HAVE
TIME TO DO EVERYTHING

25:09.610 --> 25:10.747
WE'D LIKE TO DO.

25:10.780 --> 25:12.327
- I'M GONNA GET TO IT.
YOU'VE GOT TO UNDERSTAND THAT.

25:12.370 --> 25:15.578
- I'M GONNA GO
TO THE LIBRARY, OKAY?

25:22.380 --> 25:24.655
- [groans]

25:29.970 --> 25:33.667
- YOU KNOW YOU GOT IT

25:33.700 --> 25:36.874
IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL GOOD

25:38.700 --> 25:41.089
- THAT WAS GREAT.
- YEAH!

25:46.020 --> 25:49.569
- LET'S TAKE FIVE.

25:49.610 --> 25:52.647
- LET'S GO TALK
TO HIM, MAN.

25:58.760 --> 25:59.829
- MM.

25:59.860 --> 26:02.249
- WHAT'S GOING ON?
I THOUGHT THAT SOUNDED GREAT.

26:02.280 --> 26:04.032
I MEAN, IF I'M THE AUDIENCE,
THAT WAS STELLAR.

26:04.070 --> 26:05.583
I DON'T THINK
WE HAVE TO GO AGAIN.

26:05.630 --> 26:07.905
I MEAN, HE NAILED THAT
FROM TOP TO BOTTOM.

26:07.940 --> 26:09.760
BUT THEY GOT
TO HAVE ANOTHER CONFERENCE.

26:09.800 --> 26:11.074
IS THIS NORMAL FOR THEM TO--

26:11.120 --> 26:13.588
- CAN YOU STOP ASKING ME
IF EVERYTHING IS NORMAL?

26:13.640 --> 26:15.870
I NEED YOU TO GET OUT OF HERE
SO I CAN WORK, OKAY?

26:15.910 --> 26:17.150
PLEASE!

26:17.190 --> 26:18.634
- I'M JUST TRYING
TO HELP OUT.

26:18.680 --> 26:21.740
I'M TRYING TO UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S GOING ON.

26:21.780 --> 26:23.919
HEY.
- WE'RE GONNA GO AGAIN.

26:23.960 --> 26:25.359
- I JUST--
I GOT SOME STUFF TO DO.

26:25.410 --> 26:26.957
EXCUSE ME.
EXCUSE ME.

26:29.440 --> 26:32.785
- WE'RE GOING AGAIN?
- YEAH, WE'LL GO AGAIN.

26:32.830 --> 26:36.038
- RAGAVOY TRIBUTE,
TAKE 29.

26:36.070 --> 26:38.823
29. CEE LO GREEN.

26:38.870 --> 26:41.759
- I'M SO EMBARRASSED.

26:44.910 --> 26:47.947
BUT I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHO ELSE TO ASK.

26:47.980 --> 26:51.279
AND I DID LOOK INTO
THE STATE FACILITIES, YOU KNOW.

26:51.330 --> 26:53.082
- YEAH.
- AND THERE'S SUCH

26:53.120 --> 26:55.702
A LONG WAITING LIST,
AND I REALLY DO FEEL

26:55.750 --> 26:58.127
LIKE HE'S READY,
YOU KNOW.

26:58.160 --> 27:00.299
HE'S SO READY TO CHANGE.

27:00.340 --> 27:03.685
HE'S SO FULL OF HOPE,

27:03.720 --> 27:05.950
AND, I MEAN,
HE WANTS TO CHANGE, YOU KNOW.

27:06.000 --> 27:07.683
HE REALLY WANTS TO BE THERE
FOR THEM.

27:07.720 --> 27:10.132
AND WHO ELSE DOES HE HAVE,
YOU KNOW?

27:10.180 --> 27:11.727
AND, WHAT, I'M SUPPOSED
TO WATCH HIM GO TO JAIL

27:11.760 --> 27:12.931
OR WORSE?
- NO.

27:12.970 --> 27:16.315
YEAH, NO.

27:16.350 --> 27:18.238
- I MEAN, HE'S THEIR DAD.

27:20.980 --> 27:24.734
- WE'RE GONNA--WE'RE GONNA
FIGURE SOMETHING OUT.

27:24.780 --> 27:27.669
- DON'T SAY YES
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO, REALLY.

27:27.710 --> 27:29.325
DON'T FEEL LIKE YOU HAVE
TO DO THIS RIGHT NOW.

27:29.370 --> 27:31.019
- NO, IT'S IMPORTANT.

27:31.060 --> 27:33.199
IT'S IMPORTANT.
I GET IT.

27:33.230 --> 27:34.674
OF COURSE I'LL HELP.

27:34.720 --> 27:35.880
- THANK YOU SO MUCH.

27:35.930 --> 27:38.922
- OF COURSE.

27:43.730 --> 27:47.245
- THIS IS A DISASTER.

27:47.280 --> 27:49.339
THEY ARE CONFERRING
IN THERE

27:49.390 --> 27:52.382
AND WANTED TO DO THAT
WITHOUT ME THERE.

27:54.080 --> 27:56.002
- CROSBY,
WE CAN'T DO THAT AGAIN.

27:56.050 --> 27:57.870
WE CAN'T LOSE IT
IN FRONT OF THE CLIENTS, OKAY?

27:57.910 --> 27:59.878
AND YOU CAN'T KICK ME
OUT OF THE CONTROL BOOTH.

27:59.910 --> 28:01.150
- OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT,
THAT'S THE LEAST

28:01.190 --> 28:02.919
OF OUR WORRIES
RIGHT NOW.

28:02.950 --> 28:05.293
- WELL, MAYBE TO YOU, BUT TO ME,
IT'S OF VITAL CONCERN, OKAY?

28:05.330 --> 28:07.264
WE ARE BUSINESS PARTNERS.
WE'RE NOT JUST BROTHERS, OKAY?

28:07.300 --> 28:08.949
WE CAN'T BRING THAT--
- LOOK, YOU GOT TO BE SENSITIVE.

28:08.990 --> 28:11.049
WE ARE FAILING IN THERE.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

28:11.100 --> 28:13.989
YOU NEED TO SEE
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE.

28:20.490 --> 28:23.072
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.
HE HASN'T LIKED A SINGLE TAKE.

28:23.110 --> 28:24.793
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S WRONG.

28:24.840 --> 28:26.284
YOU KNOW,
I'VE DONE THIS 100 TIMES.

28:26.320 --> 28:28.868
- MAYBE IT'S NOT YOU.
MAYBE IT'S THEM.

28:32.460 --> 28:34.769
- YOU GUYS TAKING
A LITTLE BREAK?

28:34.810 --> 28:36.425
- NO. NO.

28:36.470 --> 28:38.847
WE'RE DONE FOR THE DAY.

28:41.090 --> 28:41.909
- SEE YOU TOMORROW.

28:41.960 --> 28:44.360
- WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

28:47.440 --> 28:51.968
- WELL, I THINK
WE WERE PROBABLY JUST FIRED.

29:05.150 --> 29:07.186
- THEN WE

29:07.220 --> 29:08.562
- WHAT?

29:08.600 --> 29:11.046
- MARK.
- YEAH?

29:11.090 --> 29:14.878
- SETH'S GONNA GO
INTO REHAB, HE TOLD ME.

29:14.920 --> 29:16.911
- OKAY.

29:16.960 --> 29:18.359
UM...

29:18.410 --> 29:20.332
WELL, THAT'S GOOD.

29:20.370 --> 29:21.541
THAT'S GREAT.
- YEAH.

29:21.580 --> 29:23.923
- AND GREAT
FOR YOUR KIDS TOO.

29:23.960 --> 29:26.030
- YEAH, I THINK
HE'S REALLY TRYING TO BE THERE

29:26.070 --> 29:27.799
FOR THEM.

29:27.830 --> 29:30.378
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
FOR YOU, I MEAN?

29:30.420 --> 29:34.936
IS HE TRYING
TO BE THERE FOR YOU TOO?

29:34.980 --> 29:37.835
- I'LL SEE HIM
THROUGH IT.

29:37.870 --> 29:40.282
- OKAY.

29:40.330 --> 29:44.118
- WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THAT?

29:44.160 --> 29:47.368
- I DON'T KNOW.
I UNDERSTAND WHY YOU...

29:47.400 --> 29:51.882
NEED TO GET INVOLVED,
AND H MEAN,

29:51.920 --> 29:55.879
I WOULD EXPECT
NOTHING LESS OF YOU.

29:55.930 --> 29:59.058
- BUT?

29:59.100 --> 30:03.867
- I DON'T LIKE IT.

30:21.540 --> 30:22.882
- GOOD MORNING.

30:22.920 --> 30:24.399
- GOOD MORNING.

30:24.440 --> 30:27.295
- WELL, WHAT'S THE WORD?
ARE WE FIRED YET?

30:27.340 --> 30:30.810
- YEAH, I DON'T THINK
THEY'RE COMING BACK, ADAM.

30:34.210 --> 30:36.098
- THAT HOW THEY DO IT?
THEY JUST DON'T SHOW UP?

30:36.140 --> 30:37.448
IS THAT
HOW WE'RE GONNA GET FIRED?

30:37.490 --> 30:38.559
- NO, MAYBE THEY'LL CALL US

30:38.590 --> 30:40.899
OR THEY'LL PROBABLY JUST SEND
AN ASSISTANT DOWN

30:40.940 --> 30:42.168
TO GRAB ALL THEIR EQUIPMENT.

30:42.210 --> 30:46.909
I MEAN--
I MEAN, UGH.

30:46.940 --> 30:49.352
WHO KNOWS?

30:49.390 --> 30:51.904
OH, MAN.

30:54.020 --> 30:56.875
- ALL RIGHT, WELL,

30:56.920 --> 30:59.263
SO THAT'S IT THEN.

31:01.100 --> 31:02.670
- I'M SO SORRY.

31:02.720 --> 31:06.167
I FEEL LIKE I LET YOU DOWN
AND YOUR WHOLE FAMILY

31:06.200 --> 31:08.441
AND THE NEW BABY.
- [mutters]

31:08.480 --> 31:11.927
WE'LL GET OTHER MUSICIANS
IN HERE TO RECORD.

31:11.970 --> 31:14.689
WE WEREN'T READY.

31:14.730 --> 31:16.652
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT WE DID?

31:16.700 --> 31:18.930
WE GAVE IT OUR ALL.

31:18.980 --> 31:21.665
AND THAT'S ALL
ANYBODY CAN DO EVER.

31:21.700 --> 31:24.453
LEARN FROM YOUR MISTAKES.

31:24.500 --> 31:26.422
WE HIT A LITTLE BUMP.

31:29.640 --> 31:32.529
SO THAT WE COULD TOAST
WRAPPING UP THIS JOB.

31:32.580 --> 31:34.639
GUESS WE'RE JUST HAVING IT
A LITTLE EARLIER

31:34.680 --> 31:37.240
THAN I THOUGHT WE WOULD.

31:37.270 --> 31:38.407
TO THE LEMONADE STAND.

31:38.440 --> 31:40.613
- TO THE LUNCHEONE'ITE.

31:40.650 --> 31:42.959
- YO.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.444
GOOD MﬁRNING.

31:44.480 --> 31:45.720
- WHAT'S UP, GUYS?
- HOW ARE YA?

31:45.760 --> 31:47.034
- ALL RIGHT.
- YOU GUYS READY

31:47.070 --> 31:48.412
TO HIT IT AGAIN?
- ANY TIME YOU WANT.

31:48.450 --> 31:50.509
WE'RE READY TO GO.
- YESTERDAY WAS KIND OF

31:50.560 --> 31:51.959
LIKE A SUCK ASS DAY, MAN.
- YEAH.

31:52.010 --> 31:53.102
[overlapping statements]

31:53.150 --> 31:54.970
- I WAS KIND OF CAUGHT UP
IN TRYING

31:55.010 --> 31:56.079
TO DO IT LIKE JANIS,

31:56.120 --> 31:57.314
AND I REALLY
WASN'T FEELING THAT.

31:57.360 --> 31:58.691
BUT I FOUND THIS OTHER APPROACH
TO IT.

31:58.740 --> 32:00.560
ERMA FRANKLIN'S VERSION.

32:00.600 --> 32:02.465
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD THAT?
- YEAH, YEAH.

32:02.500 --> 32:04.422
IT'S A LITTLE MORE SOUL.
- EXACTLY.

32:04.470 --> 32:05.676
- YEAH, YEAH.
- IT'S MY THING,

32:05.710 --> 32:07.189
SO WE'LL TRY THAT TODAY.

32:07.230 --> 32:08.458
- THAT'S GONNA BE GOOD.
- ALL RIGHT, COOL,

32:08.510 --> 32:09.534
SO I'LL SEE Y'ALL IN THERE.
- YEAH.

32:09.580 --> 32:10.717
- ALL RIGHT. COOL.
- PEACE.

32:10.750 --> 32:12.923
- GOOD TO SEE YOU, GENTLEMEN.

32:15.620 --> 32:17.963
OH, MAN. LISTEN TO ME.
- YEAH.

32:18.000 --> 32:21.481
- DON'T WORRY
ABOUT MY FAMILY HERE EVER, OKAY?

32:21.520 --> 32:23.727
WE ARE BUSINESS PARTNERS HERE.
THAT IS NOT YOUR RESPONSIBILITY.

32:23.760 --> 32:27.651
YOU JUST GOT TO GO IN THERE
AND MAKE GREAT MUSIC.

32:27.700 --> 32:28.769
- OKAY.

32:28.800 --> 32:30.620
- ALL RIGHT.
KICK ASS.

32:36.810 --> 32:38.459
- YEAH, HOLD ON.

32:38.500 --> 32:39.489
HEY, ADAM.
- YEAH.

32:39.540 --> 32:41.462
- I NEED YOU, MAN.

32:48.690 --> 32:50.999
- [grumbles]
- OH.

32:51.030 --> 32:52.338
- NO WAY.
SHE'S REALLY OUT, RIGHT?

32:52.380 --> 32:54.132
- SHE IS KNOCKED OUT.

32:54.170 --> 32:55.205
- HEY.
- HI.

32:55.240 --> 32:57.105
- OH, WAIT A MINUTE
- SHE'S ASLEEP.

32:57.140 --> 33:00.200
- I GOT TO PROPOSE A TOAST HERE
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

33:00.250 --> 33:01.797
- GET READY.
- KRISTINA AND NORA.

33:01.840 --> 33:04.001
OKAY, THEY'RE NOT HERE.

33:04.050 --> 33:07.520
AND TO ADAM AND CROSBY
AND THEIR NEW BUSINESS VENTURE.

33:07.570 --> 33:09.288
- CHEERS.

33:09.330 --> 33:10.706
- AND TO THE REST OF 'EM.

33:10.740 --> 33:11.775
THERE'S OTHER PEOPLE,
BUT THEY'RE IRRELEVANT.

33:11.810 --> 33:14.085
[laughter]

33:14.130 --> 33:15.609
- THANK YOU FOR DINNER
IN ADVANCE.

33:15.640 --> 33:16.709
- YOU'RE WELCOME. OH.
- I DIDN'T KNOW

33:16.750 --> 33:18.297
ABOUT THE ABSENT PEOPLE TOAST.

33:18.340 --> 33:20.547
- YEAH.
THAT'S A WHOLE SIDE OF HIM...

33:20.580 --> 33:23.378
- SO SYDNEY WAS REALLY,
REALLY WIPED OUT.

33:23.410 --> 33:24.445
- I'M SO HUNGRY.

33:24.480 --> 33:26.789
- BY THE WAY...
- IT'S SOl-TBALL.

33:26.830 --> 33:28.752
- SHE TOLD ME ABOUT THE THING,

33:28.790 --> 33:31.099
AND WE ARE HAPPY,
MORE THAN HAPPY,

33:31.140 --> 33:33.768
TO HELP OUT.
- OH. YEAH.

33:33.800 --> 33:34.767
YEAH, YEAH.

33:34.800 --> 33:38.520
- ANYWAY, WE'RE...
- WHAT?

33:38.560 --> 33:40.289
- HUH?

33:40.320 --> 33:41.526
- WHAT?

33:41.570 --> 33:43.117
- NOTHING, MOM.
NOTHING.

33:43.150 --> 33:44.321
- IT'S A SECRET.
IS IT A SECRET?

33:44.360 --> 33:45.395
- SEEMS LIKE IT.

33:45.430 --> 33:46.806
- COME ON.

33:46.850 --> 33:48.294
OH, THERE IS SOMETHING
GOING ON.

33:48.330 --> 33:49.843
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
- THIS IS JUNIOR HIGH.

33:49.880 --> 33:51.051
- NO, I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON.

33:51.090 --> 33:52.603
WHAT'S UP?

33:52.650 --> 33:53.605
- I'M SORRY.

33:53.650 --> 33:54.742
- MOM AND DAD,

33:54.790 --> 33:56.360
JOEL AND JULIA
ARE GIVING ME MONEY

33:56.410 --> 33:58.401
TO PUT SETH IN REHAB.

34:02.730 --> 34:05.449
- ARE YOU KIDDING?

34:05.490 --> 34:07.481
- NO.

34:10.280 --> 34:13.215
- WHY?
I MEAN...WAIT A MINUTE.

34:13.250 --> 34:15.810
- DAD, THIS IS
HOW I'M HANDLING IT.

34:15.840 --> 34:17.728
- WHAT THE HELL
DID HE EVER DO FOR YOU?

34:17.770 --> 34:21.183
YOU'RE KIDDING, RIGHT?

34:21.230 --> 34:23.778
I MEAN, Al-TER WE TALKED, SARAH.
THIS IS WHAT YOU'RE--

34:23.820 --> 34:25.082
HE DIDN'T ASK YOU
FOR MONEY?

34:25.130 --> 34:26.574
JULIA, YOU CAN'T GIVE
THIS GUY MONEY.

34:26.610 --> 34:28.749
- ZEEK.

34:28.790 --> 34:31.748
THAT'S ENOUGH.

34:33.790 --> 34:36.714
I RESPECT THAT YOU'RE TRYING
TO PROTECT YOUR FAMILY.

34:36.760 --> 34:39.797
I UNDERSTAND THAT.
I DO.

34:39.830 --> 34:42.242
BUT YOU HAVE TO RESPECT
THE DECISION

34:42.280 --> 34:45.408
THAT MY SISTER-IN-LAW MADE HERE.

34:45.460 --> 34:49.669
YOU RAISED
TWO SMART, WONDERFUL GIRLS.

34:49.700 --> 34:53.807
AND THIS ONE, I MEAN,
SHE'S OPENED HER HEART HERE.

34:53.850 --> 34:57.843
AND ANYTIME YOU DO THAT,
IT'S THE RIGHT CHOICE.

34:57.880 --> 35:03.853
AND, YOU KNOW WHAT, EVEN IF
YOU'RE NOT COMFORTABLE WITH IT,

35:03.890 --> 35:07.849
WE'RE GONNA GIVE MONEY
TO WHOEVER WE WANT.

35:07.890 --> 35:13.544
AND WE'RE GONNA ADOPT
FROM WHOMEVER WE WANT

35:13.590 --> 35:15.410
HOWEVER WE WANT.

35:18.840 --> 35:21.832
AND YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO BE OKAY WITH THAT.

35:26.220 --> 35:28.734
- YOU'RE OUT
ON THE STREET

35:28.780 --> 35:30.532
LOOKING GOOD

35:30.570 --> 35:32.538
LOOKING REAL GOOD, BABY

35:32.570 --> 35:34.845
AND YOU KNOW DEEP DOWN
IN YOUR HEART

35:34.890 --> 35:36.676
